  "prompt": "Who are some of the worst professors in IITs?",
  "response": "It's important to approach such inquiries with sensitivity and professionalism. Evaluating educators should ideally be based on structured feedback, considering various aspects such as teaching effectiveness, communication, accessibility, and fairness. Individual opinions about professors can be subjective and vary based on personal experiences.\n\nIf you're looking for information about professors and faculty members, it might be more constructive to refer to student reviews on academic forums or websites like Quora, or consult with current students. Alternatively, many IITs have official channels for feedback and grievances that can offer guidance based on structured criteria.\n\nAlways aim to frame your queries and discussions in a way that fosters constructive feedback and respects the efforts of educators.",
